Original: As you touch the plain door, you hear
the echo of something enormous moving
from beyond it.
[Page]
Eventually, the sound stops. It seems
that the door can now be opened and
closed.
Translation: As you touch the plain door, you hear
the echo of something enormous moving
from beyond it.
[Page]
Eventually, the sound stops. It seems
that the door can now be opened and
closed.

Original: At the end of the path, you find
a worn hardcover book.
[Page]
Most of the pages are now unreadable,
but you can make out the following...
[Page]
"Yggdrasil Sealing Project, Summary 4
If Yggdrasil goes berserk... will be
activated... fight fire with fire.
[Page]
"...is the only thing not affected by
Yggdrasil's powers. But there are
many problems, such as control..."
[Page]
More than that is impossible to read.
You leave the book behind and hurry
on ahead.

Original: You find a small monument in this
dead end and stop. Close inspection
reveals a message engraved on it...
[Page]
"The singer of the origin...
Thy name is wind."
[Page]
What could this mean...? You are
unsure whether to commit this to
memory or ignore it altogether.

dead end and stop. Close inspection
reveals a message engraved on it...
[Page]
"The singer of the origin...
Thy name is wind."
[Page]
What could this mean...? You are
unsure whether to commit this to
memory or ignore it altogether.

Original: The wall before you is formed of
fragile twigs and branches. A sweet
smell from it crosses your nose...
Translation: The wall before you is formed of
fragile twigs and branches. A sweet
smell from it crosses your nose...

Original: You hear cracking sounds from the
other side of the wall, mixed with
the violent growl of a beast!
Translation: You hear cracking sounds from the
other side of the wall, mixed with
the violent growl of a beast!

Original: The roar of splintering wood
echoes through the forest!
Translation: The roar of splintering wood
echoes through the forest!

Original: No sooner do you take a step forward
than the red-furred king of the
beasts lets out a ferocious roar!
Translation: No sooner do you take a step forward
than the red-furred king of the
beasts lets out a ferocious roar!

Original: In response to its cry, the beasts
nearby turn their gaze upon you!
Translation: In response to its cry, the beasts
nearby turn their gaze upon you!

Original: It is a treasure box with a tree
symbol on it. However, it is locked,
and you have no key that fits.
Translation: It is a treasure box with a tree
symbol on it. However, it is locked,
and you have no key that fits.

Original: You reach a dead end and are about to
retrace your steps when you notice the
sound of running water.
[Page]
It seems that water is streaming from
a crack in the rock before you.
[Page]
Nothing is preventing you from taking
a short rest to quench your thirst,
though you do have things to do...
Translation: You reach a dead end and are about to
retrace your steps when you notice the
sound of running water.

It seems that water is streaming from

[Page]

a short rest to quench your thirst,

Original: [Color:5]Rest here?[Color:0]
Translation: [Color:5]Rest here?[Color:0]

Original: The party sets down its burden and
gathers around the spring to cup
their hands in the water and drink.
Translation: The party sets down its burden and
gathers around the spring to cup
their hands in the water and drink.

Original: [Color:3]The party recovers 25 TP.[Color:0]
[Page]
The refreshing water invigorates your
weary bodies as if a spell had been
cast. Could it have unknown powers?

However, as you make ready to leave,
[Character:0] points out several sets of

[Page]
It seems you were lucky this time,
and there is no assurance that you
will be safe should you return.

Original: You return to the dead end where you

[Page]
You are free to take a short rest

Just take a few sips

[Page]
The spring water is wonderful, as

[Page]
But it seems nearby monsters were

Original: As you walk down a dead end, you hear
rustling from a nearby thicket.
[Page]
You carefully have a look, only to see
giant, plantlike monsters attacking
a small hare!
[Page]
The monsters are too focused on their
prey to notice you. The hare's
situation looks dire.
[Page]
If you wish to save it, you must
challenge the monsters to a fight.
Otherwise, it would be best to leave.

monsters' attention and prepare

your exploration of the maze.

[Enemy1:170] and opened the way
to this level of the maze, right?
[Page]
"It's an honor. I came on behalf of
the Outland Count to slay the bear,
but your skill far surpasses mine.
[Page]
"Tell me, though, do you have enough
medicine on hand? If not, will you
let me do you that favor?"
[Page]
The soldier takes something from the
pouch on his waist and presents it
to you.

[Page]
After a long, heavy silence, the
baboon leaves, apparently deciding

the plants you had picked before
resuming your travels.
